<emphasis box="[185,293,1328,1354]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" reason="1">Remarks</emphasis>
:
</emphasis>
The specimen is similar to those described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wehe T" box="[844,999,1328,1355]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" pagination="23 - 197" refId="ref5350" refString="Wehe T (2006) Revision of scale worms (Polychaeta: Aphroditoidea) occurring in the seas surrounding the Arabian Peninsula. Part I. Polynoidae. Fauna of Arabia 22: 23 - 197." type="journal article" year="2006">Wehe (2006)</bibRefCitation>
. No subterminal swelling on antennae was observed here (
<figureCitation box="[707,788,1363,1390]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[140,212,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[183,1050,442,1574]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[181,1066,421,1603]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Lepidonotus purpureus. a anterior end, dorsal view b 3rd left elytron c microtubercles d 3rd right parapodium, anterior view e neurochaeta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3770488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3770488/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
). Moreover, notochaetae are missing on all parapodia of the specimen studied.
</paragraph>
